1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:05,340
There are currently two problems in cybersecurity reinforcing each other.

2
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:10,340
First, we have agentic engineering, which accelerates the way we ship code,

3
00:00:10,340 --> 00:00:13,740
resulting in more pressure on reviews.

4
00:00:13,740 --> 00:00:21,140
The second problem is that AI models can do pentests and cyber audits on production software

5
00:00:21,140 --> 00:00:27,140
and therefore threat actors can leverage this to find vulnerabilities faster and exploit them faster.

6
00:00:28,140 --> 00:00:33,140
This problem has been the challenge of the cyber track at the Hyper Challenge.

7
00:00:33,140 --> 00:00:37,140
And we have solved this with Zurich Verity.

8
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:42,140
What we've done is we've built a custom harness that can exploit the lab.

9
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:49,140
What you can see here is that we've found 63 findings, which each of those contain a PoC.

10
00:00:49,140 --> 00:00:53,140
So it's code you can run to verify that the finding actually works.

11
00:00:53,140 --> 00:01:02,140
It's not just a report that claims to have found something, it's always a script or a PoC that shows the findings step by step.

12
00:01:02,140 --> 00:01:07,140
We have mapped all four services and of course hope to have found all the issues.

13
00:01:07,140 --> 00:01:12,140
We cannot prove that, but we can prove the 63 issues we have found.

14
00:01:12,140 --> 00:01:15,140
But we went a step further.

15
00:01:15,140 --> 00:01:21,140
We have not only built this custom cybersecurity harness based on previous research that we've done,

16
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:29,140
it's actually also contained in a Smithers workflow, which acts based on PRs, on GitHub PRs.

17
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:31,140
So let's take a look at this.

18
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:41,140
What I can do here is in the Zurich Verity demo repository, I can create a new pull request of this demo branch, which contains a security issue.

19
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:48,140
What then happens is our workflow directly pulls this branch and does an investigation on it.

20
00:01:48,140 --> 00:02:01,140
It takes the difference between the last main state and this branch to pentest it more efficiently, so it doesn't have to map the whole codebase over and over again, so it is more efficient.

21
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:04,140
The first time we run it, it maps the whole codebase.

22
00:02:04,140 --> 00:02:08,140
What you can see here now is the pull request actually running.

23
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:15,140
But because we don't want to wait for the pull request, I've run it already before and we can quickly open that.

24
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:17,140
Now a note on speed.

25
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:23,140
Speed was not a core factor we optimized for it, because this can run in the background and finish overnight.

26
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:31,140
We didn't optimize on speed, we optimized on accuracy and provability of our issues that we find.

27
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:35,140
Here you can see the exact same PR run through Verity.

28
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:43,140
First, it can find the issues, the findings, and actually write about them.

29
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:50,140
It can let you know about what happened exactly, and then it can even block the pull request.

30
00:02:50,140 --> 00:03:00,140
So you can see here Zurich Verity review has blocked the pull request, so it cannot ship into production because it has found a critical issue.

31
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:09,140
It can also evaluate between different levels of criticality, so it can sometimes block a pull request or not, even if it has found issues.

32
00:03:09,140 --> 00:03:16,140
Here you can see the integration of Zurich Verity into a continuous pentesting loop,

33
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:24,140
so all the software you ship will continuously be pentested before it reaches production, before threat actors can attack it,

34
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:28,140
based on the custom cyber harness that we have built.

35
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:31,140
This is Zurich Verity.

